In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. emphasizes the importance of American workers and unions. He recognizes the contributions of workers throughout history, from the factory workers in World War II to the health care professionals during the pandemic. Unions have played a significant role in advocating for workers' rights, such as higher wages, better benefits, and safer working conditions. The President reiterates his commitment to being pro-worker and pro-union, mentioning the economic initiatives he has enacted, including the American Rescue Plan and various infrastructure and economic bills. He highlights the importance of creating union jobs and empowering workers. President Biden has taken actions such as signing an Executive Order banning unfair non-compete agreements and establishing a White House Task Force on Worker Organizing and Empowerment. He also calls on Congress to pass the Protecting the Right to Organize Act and the Public Service Freedom to Negotiate Act to make it easier for workers to join unions and bargain collectively. The President emphasizes the need to rebuild the economy from the bottom up and ensure equal opportunity for workers of all backgrounds. He concludes by honoring the trailblazers who have fought for workers' rights and calling for solidarity and support for all workers on Labor Day.